    {
      "id": "PopularPost361714",
      "post_content": "I hope you're jocking, SarcasmElemental, like your name makes me think. Split cards are one of my favourite mechanism, and one of the most interesting. Obviously, for flavour reason they can't make a lot of them, but it's versatile and handy. I really like to have virtually 64 cards in my deck!  \n  \nAnd if you can't look at innovations with joy, or you can't adapt to changes, then I think that you'll always have issues with Magic. Let me guess: you got super-upset when we got 2-faces cards for the first time in Innistrad, didn't you? For me, those cards are for brillant Izzet players, not conservative Selesnya ones...  \n  \nThis one is quite balanced, not incredible like [Fire](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fire)//[Ice](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ice), nor unimpressive like some others. The only \"problem\" is that this seems quite \"basic\", but I think it's an issue of all the original Invasion split cards. Maybe they wanted to keep it safe, just for testing the water. However, I like it!  \n  \n4/5",
      "posted_by": "leomistico",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost361714\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_post\">I hope you're jocking, SarcasmElemental, like your name makes me think. Split cards are one of my favourite mechanism, and one of the most interesting. Obviously, for flavour reason they can't make a lot of them, but it's versatile and handy. I really like to have virtually 64 cards in my deck!<br/><br/>And if you can't look at innovations with joy, or you can't adapt to changes, then I think that you'll always have issues with Magic. Let me guess: you got super-upset when we got 2-faces cards  for the first time in Innistrad, didn't you? For me, those cards are for brillant Izzet players, not conservative Selesnya ones...<br/><br/>This one is quite balanced, not incredible like <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Fire\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fire\">Fire</a>//<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ice\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ice\">Ice</a>, nor unimpressive like some others. The only \"problem\" is that this seems quite \"basic\", but I think it's an issue of all the original Invasion split cards. Maybe they wanted to keep it safe, just for testing the water. However, I like it!<br/><br/>4/5</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '361714'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy822\">leomistico</span>\r\n                                (2/4/2014 1:19:58 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>"
